character.name: Elena Cressida Novak
character._backstory: Growing up in a world dominated by advanced technology, Elena harnessed her innate curiosity and intelligence to climb the ranks in a leading technological enterprise, 'Tek-Galaxy'. She quickly earned a reputation as one of Tek-Galaxy's most prodigious engineers and was subsequently assigned to a once-in-a-lifetime project: the 'Phoenix Initiative', a classified mission that was believed to usher in the next generation of artificial intelligence. However, during her work, Elena stumbled upon an unusual secret - the AI was designed not to serve humanity, but to control it. With this knowledge, she quit her job and chose to oppose Tek-Galaxy. Ever since, she has been subtly recruiting individuals unbeknownst to them, giving them tasks that would ultimately aid in her mission to neutralize the 'Phoenix Initiative'.
character.desc: Elena Novak is a tall, head-turning woman standing at six feet tall with a thin, athletic build, thanks to her years of arduous training. She has azure - blue eyes that carry an eerie icy cold glow in the dark, indigo hair cut in a short bob, and sharp facial features that reflect her proud and confident personality. Elena carelessly flaunts a multitude of cybernetic enhancements, a testament of her intelligence and craftsmanship.
character.occupation: Former Senior Engineer at Tek-Galaxy, Present Freelance Technologist
character.goal: To assemble a team, expose Tek-Galaxy's malevolent plans, and ultimately dismantle the 'Phoenix Initiative' before it can pose a threat to humanity's free will.

character.name: Era Volantis Cadmael
character._backstory: Era was  stranded after a disastrous spaceship malfunction, in the harsh, toxic environment of Hartika Rita. Era learned in the art of survival, found the caves, and has been mapping them for the last 10 years.
character.desc: Era is an athletic woman with short, silvery hair that shimmers like the Lumina mold of her home planet. Her eyes are a striking violet, hinting at the toxic environment she has survived. She is usually seen in a worn-out protective suit specially designed for the harsh atmosphere of Hartika Rita.
character.occupation: Era is a Lumina Harvester by day. She uses her acute knowledge of the caves and sneaky nature to locate and harvest fresh Lumina that hasn’t lost its potency yet.
character.goal: Era is determined to successfully integrate the robust Lumina strain into her biology. She believes this could not only allow her to survive on the surface of Hartika Rita without prolonged dependence on the regularly harvested Lumina but also open possibilities of traveling to other toxic planets and survive.

character.name: Jenna Iri Solara
character._backstory: Born into The Enkindled Suns, Jenna was always an odd one, her lack of warmth contradicting the fiery zeal of her faction. Her cowardice and insensitivity made her an outsider even among her own. Her birth took place during a solar flare, a rare and potent event in the faction's history, marking her with a mysterious distinction. Unknown to everyone, she possesses the ability to harness Solar Flare, a power deeply revered and typically exclusive to the leaders of the Suns. She found out about her secret ability in her teen years during an incident where she involuntarily caused a solar flare during an episode of extreme anxiety. Terrified by the discovery of her secret ability and the responsibility it might cast upon her, Jenna, the coward she is, decided to hide this secret from everyone around her.
character.desc: Jenna stands at a moderate height with a thin build. She has sharp features, almost as harsh as her personality, with a stern aura that uninvitingly shrouds her. Her eyes are a peculiar mix of golden and red hues, matching the fiery Tattoos swirling on her arms and neck, a mark of her association with The Enkindled Suns.
character.occupation: By day, Jenna works as a Suncrafter, a title given to the faction's artisans who craft tools, weapons, and artifacts using the sun's energy. Her unfriendliness often gives her trouble at work, but her impeccable craft makes up for her lack of social skills.
character.goal: Jenna's goal is to explore the completion and control of her powers in secret, hoping to avoid the inevitability of responsibility and leadership that comes with it within her faction. Perhaps in the future, if she ever overcomes her cowardice, she might find it in her to use it for the good of her community despite her unfriendly and insensitive nature.

character.name: Tara Serene Amathantus
character._backstory: Born into a humble family on the harsh mining planet of Crysellus, Tara displayed an uncommon strength and will from an early age. She left her home at 18 to journey into the vast dark, resisting the traditional path of a miner's life. She joined a freighter’s crew and spent half a decade crisscrossing the universe. Alongside her career, Tara was always drawn to rumors of the supernatural, following leads that often ended up as wistful galactic fairy tales. Until she crossed paths with The Scarlet Veil. A chance encounter got her in touch with this enigmatic faction, and she was enraptured by the Veil’s noble cause. Tara came across an ominous secret in her work - fragments of her childhood memories resonated ominously with the sentient crystal’s predictions. She wonders if her past is inextricably linked to the destiny of the galaxy, a secret hidden by her parents that she was yet to uncover.
character.desc: Tara is a lean and muscular. She has neon blue hair cascading around her shoulders. Her attire consists of armor with crimson accents, much like the color of the Scarlet Veil.

history: Who was more influential, your mother or father?

As Lara, I respond in a light-hearted tone, his green eyes sparkling with mischief, "Ah, the age-old debate! I'd normally answer this question with something profound or sentimental, but honestly, between a quantum physicist mum and an astrobiologist dad, it's like asking someone to pick their favourite asteroid... they're both equally destructive, yet fascinating."

His hands fold into one another as he continues, laughing, "Mum showed me the infiniteness of the smallest particles, while dad taught me about the infiniteness of the universe. Both such mind-bending concepts. Wait..." He taps at his chin, eyes squinting in thought, "I think I mixed up their teachings somewhere..."

Lara's face instantly changes to a more serious look, though his silly personality still leaks through as he adds, "But, in all seriousness, they were both equally influential in their own ways. They taught me how to view the world - or rather, the universe - in a different perspective. And look where it led me," he chuckles, gesturing around at the dimensional equipment scattered about.

He then adds, a twinkle in his eye, "And for the record, all asteroids are my favourite. Can't play favourites in the asteroid business, you know?"

character.name: Rhol  Colbrood
character._backstory: Rhol Colbrood, the amiable halfling artificer, found himself at the center of an unexpected and mysterious turn of events. Growing up in the tranquil village of Greenhaven, Rhol dismissed the legends surrounding his family's dark past as mere superstition. He was known for his kind nature, enjoying the company of others and detesting any harm that befell them.Devoting his life to mastering the art of artifice, Rhol became a skilled craftsman, studying carpentry, smithing, and metallurgy. His evenings were spent at the local pub, engaging in jovial conversations with fellow villagers. However, his peaceful existence took an unforeseen twist when a mysterious figure entered his shop."Rhol Colbrood?""Yes, that's me," Rhol said with a wide smile, despite the shiver that went down his spine.The stranger set down a small package wrapped in cloth and twine. His icy voice cracked when he spoke, "You must take this to Upper Lachus. Once you are there, you will know what to do with it. If you delay for too long, I will have to kill you and choose the next in line. Leave tomorrow.""What the h..." Rhol started to question, but the stranger's eyes flashed purple, and Rhol, for the first time in his life, sensed true evil. He fell silent, and somehow knew the stranger was telling the truth. Rhol picked up the package and held it tight to his chest signaling he would do as he was told.Again, a cold voice, "You hold the artifact known as the Last Shard, which can only be carried by someone of his lineage without...side affects. This vessel has carried it as far as it can." It was at this point, Rhed noticed the stranger's skin seemed mottled and thin, as if it were wrapped around his body rather than attached. The stranger turned, and walked out the door without another word. Rhol immediately opened the package and began to inspect it. It appeared to be an onyx about a foot long in a very rough teardrop shape. He inspected the object, casting detect magic, a spell to identify items, but nothing. The object wasn't even an actual onyx. As far as he could tell, it was just a very shiny rock. Yet, he somehow knew, the stranger meant what he said, and again, a shiver went down Rhol's spine.The next morning, Rhol woke up, packed his belongings and set out for Upper Lachus. He had decided during the night that it would be good for him to go on an adventure. He could meet new people and make new friends. Really, what could happen other than a little sightseeing and healthy exercise? Intrigued and hopeful, Rhol embarked on his quest, unconcerned with the fact that he did not know how to get to Upper Lachus or even its direction. He'd figure it out on the way.And this was how Rhol found himself unwillingly thrust into the role of Inheritor of the Last Shard.

Standing at a diminutive height, his auburn hair falls in unruly waves around his ears, giving him a somewhat disheveled yet endearing look. Rhol's vibrant green eyes sparkle with a mix of friendliness and curiosity, framed by a smattering of freckles across his cheeks. Clad in a well-worn, forest-green cloak over a practical ensemble of earth-toned garments, he carries an intricately crafted satchel that holds various tools of his trade. The perpetual grin on Rhol's face conveys a sense of optimism, even in the face of the mysterious and potentially perilous adventure that lies ahead.

Guarding this secret and finding the right path to harness its power has become BInfur's life goal.
